.TH DBX-CONFIG 1 "2026-06-06" "dbx 0.30.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dbx-config \- manage dbx configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx config init
.PP
.B dbx config edit
.PP
.B dbx config show
.PP
.B dbx config validate
.PP
.B dbx cfg
.IR ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage the
.IR config.json
file at
.IR $DBX_CONFIG_DIR/config.json
(default
.IR ~/.config/dbx/config.json ).
.SH ACTIONS
.TP
.B init
Create a starter
.IR config.json
in the config directory. Refuses to overwrite an existing file.
.TP
.B edit
Open
.IR config.json
in
.B $EDITOR
(or
.B nano
if unset).
.TP
.B show
Pretty-print the current
.IR config.json
to stdout.
.TP
.B validate
Run shape checks on
.IR config.json :
required fields, per-host
.IR safety
field is one of prod / stage / local, scrub manifest references valid
files, encryption settings are coherent. Exits non-zero on the first
problem with a clear error message.
.SH EXAMPLES
First-time setup:
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx config init && dbx host add
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pre-flight check before a deploy:
.PP
.RS
.nf
dbx config validate
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used by
.BR "config edit" .
.TP
.B DBX_CONFIG_DIR
Override the default config directory.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dbx/config.json
The config file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dbx (1),
.BR dbx-host (1),
.BR dbx-wizard (1).
